criteria.driver_alignment:
Represent — verbally describes the summary table and stakeholder impacts;  
Implement — describes building the scenario summary table and formatting (units/percent, EPS decimals);  
Validate/Evolve — refers to scenario timing and alternative macro scenarios (short-term 0–12 months, 2–5 years, recession/high-growth) used to interpret visuals.

Represent — defined inputs (share price, shares outstanding, buyback size) and EPS formula/metrics;  
Implement — coded scenario calculations (buyback, dividend, debt reduction, acquisition) and produced numeric EPS/leverage outputs;  
Validate — ran sensitivities using stated assumptions (tax rate, ROIC) and showed resulting EPS changes.

Discover — defined the decision, stakeholders, and asked about agency conflicts;  
Implement — ran five-year projections comparing each option;  
Evolve/Validate/Reflect — ran scenarios/sensitivity tests, compared PE/share-price cases, and reflected on winners/losers and value transfer.
